{"content":[{"id":"1bde5c92","settings":{"flex_direction":"column","content_width":"full","padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"20","bottom":"0","left":"20","isLinked":false}},"elements":[{"id":"96dddc4","settings":{"title":"Common Causes and Treatments for Lower Back Pain\n","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"62ab875e","settings":{"editor":"Lower back pain is one of the leading causes of disability worldwide. From muscle strains to herniated discs, a variety of factors can trigger discomfort and mobility issues. In this blog, we examine the most frequent causes of lower back pain and highlight effective orthopedic treatments to help patients regain comfort and function.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"5678ef1","settings":{"title":"What is Lower Back Pain?\n","header_size":"h4","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"75f72dd1","settings":{"editor":"Lower back pain is a widespread condition that affects people of all ages and lifestyles. It refers to discomfort or stiffness in the lumbar region of the spine, which can result from various causes, ranging from muscle strain to structural issues. While most cases are acute and resolve within weeks, some develop into chronic pain that affects daily functioning and quality of life.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"12204fdc","settings":{"title":"Common Causes of Lower Back Pain\n","header_size":"h4","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"5611b65a","settings":{"title":"1. Muscle or Ligament Strain\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"77e1508d","settings":{"editor":"Sudden movements, improper lifting, or repetitive stress can overstretch or tear muscles and ligaments, leading to pain and stiffness.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"74449d2e","settings":{"title":"2. Herniated or Bulging Discs\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"6205161","settings":{"editor":"Discs act as cushions between spinal vertebrae. When one bulges or ruptures, it can compress nearby nerves, causing sharp or radiating pain.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"5d0a5139","settings":{"title":"3. Degenerative Disc Disease\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"1414776a","settings":{"editor":"As discs wear down over time, they lose their cushioning ability, leading to inflammation and chronic discomfort in the lower back.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"49996f93","settings":{"title":"4. Spinal Stenosis\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"1b51bc7c","settings":{"editor":"Narrowing of the spinal canal puts pressure on the spinal cord and nerves, causing pain, numbness, and difficulty walking or standing.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"1266301b","settings":{"title":"5. Poor Posture and Sedentary Lifestyle\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"23fa54de","settings":{"editor":"Long periods of sitting or improper posture can weaken the core and back muscles, leading to strain and imbalance.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"4fcd2eac","settings":{"title":"Effective Treatments for Lower Back Pain\n","header_size":"h4","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"488f62a7","settings":{"title":"1. Rest and Activity Modification\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"25eff9a1","settings":{"editor":"Avoiding strenuous activity for a short period and gradually resuming movement can help reduce pain and stiffness.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"67d9cbc7","settings":{"title":"2. Physical Therapy\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"1e08a3a3","settings":{"editor":"Targeted exercises improve strength, flexibility, and posture. A trained therapist can create a personalized program for faster recovery.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"4b6cfd1f","settings":{"title":"3. Medications\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"7633aabf","settings":{"editor":"Over-the-counter pain relievers like NSAIDs or muscle relaxants can manage inflammation and discomfort during acute episodes.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"49a50fcb","settings":{"title":"4. Heat and Cold Therapy\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"7ec27e0b","settings":{"editor":"Cold packs reduce inflammation in the early phase, while heat helps relax tight muscles and promote circulation during recovery.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"3e23065","settings":{"title":"5. Injections and Minimally Invasive Procedures\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"3272cbb9","settings":{"editor":"In cases of nerve involvement or chronic pain, steroid injections or nerve blocks may be used to relieve symptoms.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"694b7e1a","settings":{"title":"6. Surgery\n","header_size":"h3","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=text"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"5097a294","settings":{"editor":"When conservative treatments fail and structural issues like herniated discs or stenosis persist, surgical options such as discectomy or spinal fusion may be considered.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"320aeb1d","settings":{"title":"When to See a Specialist\n","header_size":"h4","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"4da9b8ae","settings":{"editor":"If lower back pain lasts more than a few weeks, worsens over time, or is accompanied by leg weakness, numbness, or bowel\/bladder issues, it's crucial to consult an orthopedic or spine specialist for accurate diagnosis and treatment.\n\n","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"3d638318","settings":{"title":"Conclusion","header_size":"h4","__globals__":{"title_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"heading","elType":"widget"},{"id":"4b6ac7e8","settings":{"editor":"<p>Lower back pain can be disruptive but is often manageable with timely intervention and the right care. Identifying the cause and adopting a tailored treatment approach\u2014whether through physical therapy, medication, or advanced procedures\u2014can significantly improve comfort and mobility.<\/p>\n<p>Consult a spine specialist to determine the most effective treatment plan for your lower back pain and prevent future episodes.<\/p>","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":18,"sizes":[]},"typography_line_height":{"unit":"px","size":28,"sizes":[]}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"container"}],"settings":{"template":"default"},"metadata":[]}